helpdesk-ticket.description-html:

Rebecca Ploeckelman
Director of Human Resources
Milwaukee School of Engineering
1025 N. Broadway
Milwaukee, WI 53202

helpdesk-note.body:
HI Becky,
So there are 2 settings. One for when you are not on the phone and it doesn't get answered, and one for when you are on the phone so the line is in use. I set both to ring to 7132. If they don't get picked up there either, like after hours or some such,it will then dump users into your voicemail.
Tony

Several of you have already started on the ALEKS Program – good job.  I have a reminder for you.  It is very important that you take the initial assessment prior to starting the actual ALEKS Program.  You should have received the initial assessment (placement) code on Friday.  If you did not get it, or are having trouble, please response to this e-mail as quickly as possible. 
 
Also, please be aware of the following announcement that we just got…….
 
Notice of Emergency Downtime (Blackboard)
Please be advised that Blackboard will be unavailable from 2:00am – 4:00am on Tuesday, June 14th. This period of downtime will be scheduled for emergency updates to Blackboard.
Again, welcome to MSOE and the Carter Academy Program class of 2020!!!  Looking forward to hearing from you.
 
Betty

helpdesk-ticket.subject: RE: Senior Laptop Gifting Procedure
helpdesk-ticket.description:
Hi there,
I completely forgot about this… what can I do and when can I bring it in?
Thanks,
Landon Mara
From: Helpdesk Sent: Friday, May 27, 2016 2:21 PM Subject: Senior Laptop Gifting Procedure
[cid:image001.png@01D1C67E.86663840]
Congratulations!
My records indicate that you will participate in the upcoming commencement exercise for this quarter and that you also participate in the Technology Program.
As a graduate of MSOE, you get to keep the laptop currently assigned to you upon graduation with a Bachelors degree; however, all MSOE licensed software must be removed. The process of removing MSOE licensed software will begin on May 27th and will run through June 10th. Special arrangements can be made if you are unable to participate during the slotted time frame; however you must notify IT in advance of your situation. Please come to Helpdesk so that all MSOE licensed software can be removed. If you have already removed this software, it is still necessary for you to have your laptop audited and the owner status changed from MSOE to you as the owner. Failure to have our records updated to reflect that you have become the owner of this laptop could result in continued Technology Program charges being applied to your account and the delayed distribution of your diploma.
Additionally, should you need any repairs to your laptop; we can provide this service for you before you leave the campus. Please allow a minimum of 5 - 7 days for any repairs that need to be done on your laptop. If time does not allow for you to leave your laptop with IT for service, then you can take your laptop to an authorized HP service center to have repairs done. Your laptop has a one year warranty remaining. The warranty sticker can be found on the bottom of your laptop.

From: Helpdesk
Sent: Friday, May 27, 2016 2:21 PM
Subject: Senior Laptop Gifting Procedure
 
 
 
Congratulations!
 
 
My records indicate that you will participate in the upcoming commencement exercise for this quarter and that you also participate in the Technology Program.
 
As a graduate of MSOE, you get to keep the laptop currently assigned to you upon graduation with a Bachelors degree; however, all MSOE licensed software must be removed. The process of removing MSOE licensed software will begin on May 27th and will run through June 10th.  Special arrangements can be made if you are unable to participate during the slotted time frame; however you must notify IT in advance of your situation. Please come to Helpdesk so that all MSOE licensed software can be removed.    If you have already removed this software, it is still necessary for you to have your laptop audited and the owner status changed from MSOE to you as the owner.  Failure to have our records updated to reflect that you have become the owner of this laptop could result in continued Technology Program charges being applied to your account and the delayed distribution of your diploma. 
 
Additionally, should you need any repairs to your laptop; we can provide this service for you before you leave the campus. Please allow a minimum of 5 - 7 days for any repairs that need to be done on your laptop. If time does not allow for you to leave your laptop with IT for service, then you can take your laptop to an authorized HP service center to have repairs done.  Your laptop has a one year warranty remaining.  The warranty sticker can be found on the bottom of your laptop. 
 
Again congratulations on your accomplishment and we wish you much success as you leave the halls of MSOE and move onto to other opportunities.
 
MSOE Technology Program

helpdesk-note.body:
Merged from ticket 9047 Subject: Undergraduate Computers Description:
Hi, I had just put a ticket in and it got resolved. I have a few other questions though.
Is the entire hard drive swiped? If so why is it? Do you have an estimate for when the computers will be returned? (An original ticket was never made either)
Is the hard drive recoverable? When a friend had attempted to back up his computer, it had said it was. We then discovered last night it never actually backed it up, meaning he doesnt have the last 2 years worth of information. What is needed is the information on his desktop and his resume. Everything else is not that important.
Thank you for your time.
Kayla Helbig

Kayla Helbig

helpdesk-note.body:
Ticket with id
9047
is merged into this ticket.
helpdesk-note.body-html: Ticket with id 9047 is merged into this ticket.

helpdesk-note.body:
Hey Kayla,
Yes, the entire hard drive is wiped. This is done because there is software on all MSOE laptops (including the version and license of Windows 7) that is licensed to MSOE for current students to use. It would constitute fraud for MSOE to allow graduates to keep the software that is installed when MSOE hands out computers. That is why we wipe the hard drive.
The entire process takes less than 2 hours.
Backing up your personal data is your personal responsibility. MSOE IT is happy to assist you in doing this, but ultimately it is the responsibility of the user.
We really would need more information about how your friend backed up his laptop. Where did he save the backup? 566056

helpdesk-note.body:
Hi Stefan Last, Issue: http://helpdesk.msoe.edu/helpdesk/tickets/9055
When logging into your MSOE mail box you need to enter your email address instead of your username. In this case, you would enter lasts@msoe.edu and then your password. Different MSOE websites will require either your username, lasts, or your email address, lasts@msoe.edu, when logging in, so it is important to double check what each website is asking for. Please try logging into yoru mailbox at outlook.com/msoe.edu entering your email and password. I will be considering this issue resolved, however, if you have any additional questions or concerns please feel free to contact us. Any feedback you would be willing to provide in the attached survey would be appreciated
Thanks, Thomas Schleich helpdesk@msoe.edu 414-277-7288

Hi fennigko, Issue: http://helpdesk.msoe.edu/helpdesk/tickets/9063
I have included instructions for adding network printers below, and will be marking this incident resolved. However, if you have any questions or concerns please feel free to contact us. Any feedback you would be willing to provide in the attached survey would be appreciated.

helpdesk-note.body: This is an issue involving hub merger. He just needed to merge his personal account, then he was able to get in.
helpdesk-note.body-html: This is an issue involving hub merger. He just needed to merge his personal account, then he was able to get in.

helpdesk-note.body:
Dear Anirudh and Financial Aid Staff,
This happened as a result of Anirudh having a personal email account on the Hub. Students with personal accounts from before they became students are required to merge them with their current account before their student Community account is fully accessible. Anirudh visited the helpdesk and we were able to figure out that this was the cause.
This issue is considered resolved. Feel free to reply with any additional queries.
Have a great day!

helpdesk-note.body:
FYI I was able to get it into the menu bar moments after I had sent the request (by using the add-ons dialog). Since I had already installed the trial version and linked it to the MS Office suite, all I had to do was open an equation (inside of MS Word) and select the registration option from the help tab. If you do that, you get the dialog box.
Ed Griggs
Bottom line: you may close the ticket.

On Thu, Jun 16, 2016 at 5:28 PM -0500, "Corey Lardinois" <Corey.Lardinois@lardinois.us<mailto:Corey.Lardinois@lardinois.us>> wrote:
I had started conversation with Paul Fabian over a year ago. He was on-board with the idea, but wanted to wait until after summer when he had a chance to upgrade bandwidth. At the time MLH didn’t have switches capable of extending an Internet DMZ to the dorm (not sure if they didn’t have VLAN capable switches or what), so the plan had been to use an IP on the student network.
From there we were supposed to work with Jason Kann (cabling guy) to get a drop installed, but after three emails he never responded and it went nowhere. I’m not sure if any of those guys are still around (do you guys know?), but I’ll reach out to them and see if we can get this kicked off. I believe there’s a telecom closet directly below the repeater cage, so it would be a no-brainer to install a run of fiber up from where I think the network switches are. I say fiber because our equipment is subject to lightening and I want the glass to maintain a galvanic separation from their equipment as to not be blamed for any lightening damage.
I have a Raspberry Pi ready to go with Asterisk and have an Allstar node number already assigned/configured. I’ll probably request an EchoLink number as well and configure Asterisk to add that as well. The Pi will connect to both the VHF and UHF repeaters with the intention that we can also use it to link the VHF and UHF repeaters together.
More to come,
Corey
From: Koppenhaver, Jeremy [mailto:koppenhaverj@msoe.edu] Sent: Monday, June 13, 2016 8:57 PM To: Corey Lardinois Subject: Fw: Internet Connection for the W9HHX repeater

Cameron,
I looked a little bit more into the requirements and it looks like it would need a static IP as well as a few ports. Allstar does use port 4569 and if we wanted to link it to the echolink network we would also need ports 5198 and 5199. I don't know if this is a possibility or not I hadn't thought about it colliding with VOIP systems.
Jeremy Koppenhaver

From there we were supposed to work with Jason Kann (cabling guy) to get a drop installed, but after three emails he never responded and it went nowhere.  I’m not sure if any of those guys are still around (do you guys know?), but I’ll reach out to them and see if we can get this kicked off.  I believe there’s a telecom closet directly below the repeater cage, so it would be a no-brainer to install a run of fiber up from where I think the network switches are.  I say fiber because our equipment is subject to lightening and I want the glass to maintain a galvanic separation from their equipment as to not be blamed for any lightening damage.
 
I have a Raspberry Pi ready to go with Asterisk and have an Allstar node number already assigned/configured.  I’ll probably request an EchoLink number as well and configure Asterisk to add that as well.  The Pi will connect to both the VHF and UHF repeaters with the intention that we can also use it to link the VHF and UHF repeaters together.
 
More to come,
Corey

Jeremy Koppenhaver

Also allstar, I believe, runs over the VOIP udp port 4569, which might be a problem if we need to pass it to the internet. Let me know and I can get that ticket written up.

helpdesk-note.body:
Hi Mark,
It is my understanding that the Custom folder and Additional Reports folder are specific places for certain reports in Jenzabar. Any other reports that you use outside of Jenzabar (ones you run directly in InfoMaker) should probably be kept in the Misc folder under D:\MSOE\Jenzabar\Reports\Misc\Enrollment Pibbles. This is the way it was set up when we moved to the cloud. We probably use the Misc folder for all other reports because it acts as a safeguard to prevent any changes to some vital reports in Custom and Additional Reports. The Misc folder name was discussed at a previous JAT meeting though. We were asked to change the name and add security to each department's folder. We will be doing that as we are able to.
Jasmine

helpdesk-note.body-html:
Hi Mark, 
It is my understanding that the Custom folder and Additional Reports folder are specific places for certain reports in Jenzabar. Any other reports that you will use outside of Jenzabar (ones you run directly in InfoMaker) should probably be kept in the Misc folder under D:\MSOE\Jenzabar\Reports\Misc\Enrollment Pibbles. This is the way it was set up when we moved to the cloud. We probably use the Misc folder for other reports because it acts as a safeguard to prevent any changes to some vital reports in Custom and Additional Reports. 
The Misc folder name was discussed at a previous JAT meeting though. We were asked to change the name and add security to each department's folder. We will be doing that as we are able to. 
Jasmine

Yes, I can see reports.  Thanks!  And, at some time do we want to standardize the location of the .pbl files?  Enrollment .pbl files are currently located under miscilaneous along with development.  I am just wondering if we want to fix the location convention now so that it will be easier in the future and everything will be consistent.
Thanks!
Mark

helpdesk-ticket.subject: Email Hacked?
helpdesk-ticket.description:
I received an email from myself to myself that I never sent out. I think it is spam?
How can I correct this?
[cid:image001.jpg@01D1CB09.E793C3A0]
helpdesk-ticket.description-html:
I received an email from myself to myself that I never sent out. I think it is spam?
 
How can I correct this?

helpdesk-note.body:
Hi Dr. Joshua Schultz, Issue: http://helpdesk.msoe.edu/helpdesk/tickets/9132
If you could send the Internet Header Information from the email. I am including the instructions below.
1) Double click the email so it opens in a new window. 2) In the new window, select File 3) Select Properties. 4) Please Copy and send the Internet Headers Box to us
Thanks, Thomas Schleich helpdesk@msoe.edu 414-277-7288
helpdesk-note.body-html:
Hi Dr. Joshua Schultz,

Issue: http://helpdesk.msoe.edu/helpdesk/tickets/9132

If you could send the Internet Header Information from the email. I am including the instructions below.

1) Double click the email so it opens in a new window.
2) In the new window, select File
3) Select Properties.
4) Please Copy and send the Internet Headers Box to us

Thanks,
Thomas Schleich
helpdesk@msoe.edu
414-277-7288

Issue: http://helpdesk.msoe.edu/helpdesk/tickets/9132
I received an email from myself to myself that I never sent out. I think it is spam?
 
How can I correct this?

helpdesk-note.body:
Hi Josh,
I received the attachment. Unfortunately I was unable to determine who the real sender was. The email that was sent was only received by you. I also confirmed your email was not hacked. The real sender made it look like the email came from you when it actually didn't (this is called spoofing).
We do have checks in place that prevent spoofing but sometimes emails can sneak through. Since there is not much more I can do with this so I am going to mark this ticket as resolved. Please continue to forward any suspicious emails to us so we can investigate.
Thanks Mike Issue: http://helpdesk.msoe.edu/helpdesk/tickets/9132
I received an email from myself to myself that I never sent out. I think it is spam?
How can I correct this?
helpdesk-note.body-html:
Hi Josh,

I received the attachment.  Unfortunately I was unable to determine who the real sender was.  The email that was sent was only received by you.  I also confirmed your email was not hacked.  The real sender made it look like the email came from you when it actually didn't (this is called spoofing). 

We do have checks in place that prevent spoofing but sometimes emails can sneak through.  Since there is not much more I can do with this so I am going to mark this ticket as resolved.  Please continue to forward any suspicious emails to us so we can investigate.

Thanks
Mike

helpdesk-ticket.subject: FW: Information Technology - Notice of Downtime (GETfunds)
helpdesk-ticket.description:
In case you get a call or email regarding GET during this downtime, here’s an email received from CBORD tech as to what may happen if someone tries to use GET during the downtime. This is definitely not ideal, but wanted to let you know.
Please inform students as to when Get will be back up. This is an estimated time.
“Our current DNS provider does not provide a custom “Under Construction” or “Down for Maintenance” message.
Therefore, customers accessing GET with a web browser will get a timeout message from their browser.
On Android they will likely see the GET logo pulsing indefinitely as the app tries to connect to the backend.
On iOS it will likely be an indefinite loading screen, a blank list of institutions, or a timeout/error message.
It also depends on whether the user has previously logged in or not and whether their school has GET My Card or not.
In all cases we think it will hang/timeout, but they may see different screens when that happens.
We know that these user experiences are not ideal. Unfortunately due to the nature of this move across datacenters we have very few options for managing the user experience.”
Thanks
Sheila Barber Campus Card Administrator Milwaukee School of Engineering 1025 N Broadway CC435 Milwaukee WI 53202 Work: (414) 277-7460
From: Helpdesk Sent: Tuesday, June 14, 2016 4:40 PM To: All Faculty <AllFaculty@msoe.edu>; All Staff <AllStaff@msoe.edu>; All Students <AllStudents@msoe.edu> Subject: Information Technology - Notice of Downtime (GETfunds) Importance: High

Impact: How am I affected?
During this time you will not be able to add money to your Raider Plan, look at transaction history, or check out the list of off-campus merchants.
No MSOE employees nor any MSOE correspondence will ever ask you for your account password. MSOE IT Helpdesk (414)277-7288 helpdesk.msoe.edu CC Greatroom
Helpdesk Hours Mon-Thurs: 7:30a-7:00p Fri: 7:30a-5:00p Sat-Sun: 10:00a-6:00p Summer Hours Mon-Fri: 8:00a-4:30p
helpdesk-ticket.description-html:
In case you get a call or email regarding GET during this downtime, here’s an email received from CBORD tech as to what may happen if someone tries to use GET during the downtime.  This is definitely not ideal, but wanted to let you know.
Please inform students as to when Get will be back up.  This is an estimated time.
 
“Our current DNS provider does not provide a custom “Under Construction” or “Down for Maintenance” message. 
 
Therefore, customers accessing GET with a web browser will get a timeout message from their browser.

On Android they will likely see the GET logo pulsing indefinitely as the app tries to connect to the backend.  

On iOS it will likely be an indefinite loading screen, a blank list of institutions, or a timeout/error message.
 
It also depends on whether the user has previously logged in or not and whether their school has GET My Card or not.
 
In all cases we think it will hang/timeout, but they may see different screens when that happens.

We know that these user experiences are not ideal. Unfortunately due to the nature of this move across datacenters we have very few options for managing the user experience.”
 
Thanks

helpdesk-ticket.description:
Hello,
The telephones in GM 317 and GM 319 are going to have to be reconfigured.
The one phone in GM 317 needs to be reassigned to Dr. Andrew McAninch, a new faculty member in the General Studies Department. The phone used to belong to Gary Boelkins and there are currently messages left on the phone that need to be cleared.
There are several telephones in GM 319 and all but one can be removed. The remaining phone needs to be reassigned to Dr. Lauren Beverung, another new faculty member in the General Studies Department. I suspect both phones will need to be assigned new numbers.
Also, part-time faculty who were located in GM 319 have been moved as follows:
Elizabeth Clark, Cyndie Weis, and Jessica Schnur will move to GM 304, along with Margeret Dwyer and Timothy Gaynor.
Hannah Haase, Yazmene Thomas, and Virigina Reinmuller will move to GM 217, along with Annemarie Fleishman, Amy Murre, and Mark Zimmermann.
Please let me know if you have any questions or require more information.
Thank you.
Rose

helpdesk-ticket.subject: Alumni Account creation failing
helpdesk-ticket.description: Puneet is trying to create his alumni email account but when he attempts to create the account it give him an error and says "under process" or something similar. Is his account craeted? what is the username? Can we provide it early since he needs two more classes before officially graduating (if that is the problem), so that he can apply for jobs with an MSOE email?
helpdesk-ticket.description-html: Puneet is trying to create his alumni email account but when he attempts to create the account it give him an error and says "under process" or something similar. Is his account craeted? what is the username? Can we provide it early since he needs two more classes before officially graduating (if that is the problem), so that he can apply for jobs with an MSOE email?

helpdesk-note.body:
Hi Puneet,
In order for the system to create your MSOE alumni email account the system has to see a date degree conferred for your account. Even if you have gone to commencement or just need a few credits, the system wont give you a date degree conferred until you have all the necessary requirements to officially graduating. Until then the system will always fail the creation process. If you have any other questions or concerns please let me know.
Best Regards, Sam West MSOE IT Alumni Email Team Issue: http://helpdesk.msoe.edu/helpdesk/tickets/9168

helpdesk-ticket.subject: XML Validator
helpdesk-ticket.description:
Hello,
Do we have an XML validator tool? I am looking for one in order to problem solve issues with our ACA submission to the IRS. If we do not have one, I would like to download one but want to make sure we are using something that is safe.
Please let me know if you have something I can use. The submission to the IRS is due June 30, 2016.
Thank you.
Tracy Buczek Payroll & Benefits Coordinator 1025 N Broadway Milwaukee, WI 53202 Ph: (414) 277-7136 buczek@msoe.edu<mailto:buczek@msoe.edu> [xlogo-msoe_75.png.pagespeed.ic]
helpdesk-ticket.description-html:
Hello,
 
Do we have an XML validator tool?  I am looking for one in order to problem solve issues with our ACA submission to the IRS.  If we do not have one, I would like to download one but want to make sure we are using something that is safe.
 
Please let me know if you have something I can use.  The submission to the IRS is due June 30, 2016.
 
Thank you.
 
Tracy Buczek
Payroll & Benefits Coordinator
1025 N Broadway
Milwaukee, WI 53202
Ph:  (414) 277-7136
buczek@msoe.edu

helpdesk-note.body:
Hi Tracy Buczek, Issue: http://helpdesk.msoe.edu/helpdesk/tickets/9189
There are plenty of tools that can validate XML files. I would recommend using Notepad++ which can check the syntax for you. I believe that Visual Studio can also validate XML. Web based tools also exist that can do it.
Here is the notepad ++ homepage https://notepad-plus-plus.org/
Thanks,
Cameron Wilson Information Technology
Assistant System Admin 414-277-7288 helpdesk@msoe.edu

helpdesk-ticket.description:

Sent from my Verizon 4G LTE smartphone
-------- Original message -------- From: "Bowen, Michael" <bowenm@msoe.edu> Date: 6/26/16 3:54 PM (GMT-06:00) To: "Gagliano, Richard" <gagliano@msoe.edu> Subject: Re: CABLE ISSUES? CABLE CHANNEL LINE-UP and Additional Information - Grohmann Tower Apartments
Hey Rick,
The past couple weeks and days the Internet in my room has been spotty, I can't get MSOE or MSOE guest in my room and the line in that is attached to my router does not connect me to the Internet. Today I tried to watch cable, which I rarely do and found out that I could not watch it like I have in the past. My apartment number is 906, phone number is 4145875679, and email is bowenm@msoe.edu<mailto:bowenm@msoe.edu>. If you could let me know if this is a common problem or not really that would be great. Whenever you have a second I would appreciate hearing back from you.
Thanks,
Michael Bowen
Sent from my iPhone
On Jun 24, 2016, at 11:11 AM, Gagliano, Richard <gagliano@msoe.edu<mailto:gagliano@msoe.edu>> wrote:
<image003.jpg> <image005.png>
TOWER RESIDENTS:
IF YOU ARE STILL HAVING CABLE ISSUES, PLEASE READ THIS MESSAGE FROM TIME WARNER CABLE. If you are still having issues after you try this, please send me your name, apartment number, phone, and email…which I will forward to them directly. Their techs will then reach out to you and schedule a time with you to come by and try and repair. Please note that “cable boxes” will not work and are not available for this complex.
In addition, I have attached the NEW cable channel line-up.
Thanks for your continued patience.
rbg
--------------------------------------------
​Richard,
Please see attached, it may be helpful to get this distributed to each unit at Grohmann Tower.
The building [Grohmann Tower Apartments] is now on the very specific College and University channel line-up. The line-up that Colleges and Universities is not the same as what people get in their homes, it is only for Colleges and Universities. and it is delivered differently than is delivered anywhere else, but for Colleges and Universities. This line-up had a lot of market research behind it, the channels are what a # of Colleges and Universities across the country wanted. It is a "boxless" solution, TWC or Charter Boxes are not necessary, they would not work. This line-up and specific delivery system was enabled so that Colleges and Universities would NOT have to keep track of, or be responsible for, Channel selector boxes of any kind.
With the vast majority of TV's in the marketplace, in order to receive this line-up, the TV must be direct connected to the cable line extending from the wall plate. Once connected, the TV must be re-programmed or re-tuned. in most cases , the resident can do this themselves. "Menu-Cable Function - Auto-program" does the trick, in most cases.
Last weekend, out Techs Op guys visited 7 apartments at the building, and they reprogrammed TV's for residents. And the results were fine, from what I was told. We are absolutely happy to visit other units at the facility - just tell us which ones, along with a name and phone # so we can make arrangements to enter the unit and help the resident.
On the comments about residents being told to get boxes, well, that is unfortunate. I do not doubt for a moment someone may have told one of your residents that though. The vast majority of properties in our Service area do need boxes to continue getting service - and there quite easily may have been confusion with the address. Your MSOE facility does NOT need, nor will they work, any digital adapter boxes connected to TV's.
If you are getting complaints , or if services are not working, please, please give us the name of the residents, and the unit #, and telephone #, and we will make contact, and get them squared away. It seems obvious that people at the property are coming to you - which ones?
There are some TV's in the marketplace that do not have digital tuners in them. Generally, these are older TV's. if a TV does not have a digital tuner, they will not be able to accept this channel line-up. We are finding that these are very few and far between. We just have to suggest that a person call the manufacturer - to see what (if a newer TV manufactured in the last 4 years or so) can be done. Over at Marquette for example, one resident had just purchased an ELEMENT TV, it did not work,it did not have a digital tuner, she returned it and got a different TV. But, again, if a unit or resident is having problems, we are happy to get someone there to assist.
If you or your property management have questions, or know of a resident that needs help, please reach out to us, me or Lita, and we will do our best to get them some help. Name, unit #, telephone # is essential. For the time being, i ask that residents do not call the main TWC or Charter office. the rest of our Wisconsin Service area is undergoing a massive transition to an all digital delivery system, and someone easily could be told "get a digital box" again.
Thank you,
​Jim Fraser | Manager, Spectrum Community Solutions
Wisconsin, Kansas City MO, KS & Lincoln NE areas
1320 N Dr. Martin Luther King Jr dr. |Milwaukee, WI 53212 <image001.png> <MSOE CLU Letter.docx>

Issue: http://helpdesk.msoe.edu/helpdesk/tickets/9265
IT Staff:
 
I teach a fall quarter course (BE-1005) that uses Multisim. Last fall, we were used Multisim 13 installed as part of NI-Labview 2012.
What version of this software do you plan to support next fall?
 
Dr. Tritt

helpdesk-note.body:
Mike:
It appears the current version is Multisim 14 and I always like to start academic years using the most recent available software versions. However, this should not be solely my decision. A number of EECS faculty use Multisim and we don’t want to surprise anyone with a new version (unless the old one can be kept available). I’m copying Steve Williams on this message as he may be able to provide a departmental perspective or at least get other key Multisim users involved in the discussion.
The intent of my original message was to understand current IT plans are rather than attempt to influence these plans.
I glanced at the “what’s new” information for Multisim 14. There does not appear to be any compelling improvements, with the possible exception of their improved “Probes” functionality. Here is what they say about it:
The probe functionality has been redesigned in Multisim 14 to allow additional measurement functionalities in Multisim. Whether you’re learning for the first time about an inverting amplifier circuit or designing a sophisticated switching power supply, the new probes will help you gain knowledge of your circuit performance quickly and easily. The new Voltage, Current, Power, and Digital probes provide: § A clear and convenient way of acquiring common measurements, such as voltages, branch current, and power. § Automation of the output variable selection process in analyses (such as Transient and AC Sweep); after an analysis is run, variables from probes are automatically plotted in the Grapher. § Easy annotation of important nodes on the schematic. I use probes in my BE-1005 course, but thought they worked fine in the previous version.
Charles
